parameters.name: PipelineName
parameters.description: The name or Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the pipeline.

parameters.name: PipelineParameters
parameters.description: Contains a list of pipeline parameters. This list can be empty. (dict) --- Assigns a value to a named Pipeline parameter. The name of the parameter to assign a value to. This parameter name must match a named parameter in the pipeline definition. The literal value for the parameter.

nested_params.name: Name
nested_params.description: The name of the parameter to assign a value to. This parameter name must match a named parameter in the pipeline definition.

nested_params.name: Value
nested_params.description: The literal value for the parameter.

parameters.name: ClientRequestToken
parameters.description: A unique, case-sensitive identifier that you provide to ensure the idempotency of the operation. An idempotent operation completes no more than once. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: ParallelismConfiguration
parameters.description: This configuration, if specified, overrides the parallelism configuration of the parent pipeline for this specific run. The max number of steps that can be executed in parallel.

nested_params.name: MaxParallelExecutionSteps
nested_params.description: The max number of steps that can be executed in parallel.

parameters.name: SelectiveExecutionConfig
parameters.description: The selective execution configuration applied to the pipeline run. SourcePipelineExecutionArn (string) --- The ARN from a reference execution of the current pipeline. Used to copy input collaterals needed for the selected steps to run. The execution status of the pipeline can be either Failed or Success. This field is required if the steps you specify for SelectedSteps depend on output collaterals from any non-specified pipeline steps. For more information, see Selective Execution for Pipeline Steps. A list of pipeline steps to run. All step(s) in all path(s) between two selected steps should be included. (dict) --- A step selected to run in selective execution mode. The name of the pipeline step.

nested_params.name: SourcePipelineExecutionArn
nested_params.description: The ARN from a reference execution of the current pipeline. Used to copy input collaterals needed for the selected steps to run. The execution status of the pipeline can be either Failed or Success. This field is required if the steps you specify for SelectedSteps depend on output collaterals from any non-specified pipeline steps. For more information, see Selective Execution for Pipeline Steps.

nested_params.name: SelectedSteps
nested_params.description: A list of pipeline steps to run. All step(s) in all path(s) between two selected steps should be included.

nested_params.name: StepName
nested_params.description: The name of the pipeline step.

nested_items.name: PipelineExecutionArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the pipeline execution.
